  "text": "Kubernetes does not use sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime in its core codebase. Instead, it uses a custom controller management pattern based on work queues and informers. Here is how controllers register and reconcile in kubernetes/kubernetes:\n\n## Controller Registration Pattern\n\nControllers are registered through the ControllerDescriptor system defined in cmd/kube-controller-manager/app/controllermanager.go:\n\n1. **NewControllerDescriptors()** (line 495) - Registers all known controllers. Each controller descriptor contains:\n   - A unique name (e.g., 'endpointslice-controller')\n   - An initFunc that initializes the controller\n   - Optional aliases\n   - Feature gate requirements\n\n2. **ControllerDescriptor** - Contains:\n   - name: string\n   - aliases: []string  \n   - initFunc: function that creates and starts the controller\n   - requiresSpecialHandling: bool (for controllers like ServiceAccountTokenController that must start first)\n\n3. **ControllerContext** (line 366) - Passed to each controller's initFunc containing:\n   - ClientBuilder: for creating API clients\n   - InformerFactory: SharedInformerFactory for watching resources\n   - ObjectOrMetadataInformerFactory: for metadata access\n   - RESTMapper: for resource mapping\n   - ResyncPeriod: function generating sync intervals\n\n## Controller Startup Flow\n\n1. **StartControllers()** (line 662) - Main function that starts all registered controllers\n2. **StartController()** (line 710) - Starts an individual controller by:\n   - Checking feature gate requirements\n   - Calling the controller's initFunc\n   - Starting worker goroutines\n\n## Reconciliation Pattern (Non-Controller-Runtime)\n\nInstead of the controller-runtime Reconciler interface, Kubernetes uses:\n\n### Work Queue Pattern (Standard)\nSeen in staging/src/k8s.io/sample-controller/controller.go:\n- Controller struct with:\n  - workqueue.RateLimitingInterface for queuing work items\n  - Informer synced callbacks for coordinating startup\n  - Event recorder for recording cluster events\n\n- Run(ctx, workers) - Main loop that:\n  - Waits for informer caches to sync (WaitForCacheSync)\n  - Launches N worker goroutines\n  - Each worker calls runWorker -> processNextWorkItem -> syncHandler\n\n- syncHandler(ctx, objectRef) - The reconciliation logic that:\n  - Gets the object from lister\n  - Compares desired vs actual state\n  - Performs operations to converge state\n  - Handles errors with backoff/requeuing\n\n### Endpoint Reconciler Pattern (Custom)\nSeen in pkg/controlplane/reconcilers/reconcilers.go:\n- EndpointReconciler interface with methods:\n  - ReconcileEndpoints() - Reconciles master endpoints\n  - RemoveEndpoints() - Removes endpoint entries\n  - StopReconciling() - Cleanly stops reconciliation\n  - Destroy() - Cleans up resources\n\n- Implementations:\n  - masterCountEndpointReconciler (instancecount.go) - Reconciles based on expected master count\n  - leaseEndpointReconciler (lease.go) - Stores endpoint info using leases\n\n### Apiserver Reconciler Pattern\nSeen in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/reconcilers/peer_endpoint_lease.go:\n- PeerEndpointLeaseReconciler interface for managing apiserver peer endpoints\n- PeerEndpointLeaseController struct with:\n  - Run(stopCh) - Main reconciliation loop\n  - UpdatePeerEndpointLeases() - Periodic reconciliation function\n  - Fixed interval polling (not event-driven)\n\n## Key Differences from Controller-Runtime\n\n1. **No Manager**: Controllers are started directly, not registered with a manager\n2. **No Reconcile Interface**: Controllers implement custom Run/sync methods, not Reconcile(ctx, Request) (Result, error)\n3. **Work Queue Based**: Uses client-go's workqueue.RateLimitingInterface, not controller-runtime's reconcile.Request/Result\n4. **Manual Startup**: Controllers initialize event handlers and workers directly via cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs\n5. **No SetupWithManager**: Controllers don't have a SetupWithManager method - registration happens through ControllerDescriptor\n\nThe actual controller-runtime library (sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime) is only mentioned in a test comment (test/integration/cloudprovider/ccm_test.go:304) and is not used in the core Kubernetes codebase. Projects like kubebuilder use controller-runtime for custom controllers, but Kubernetes itself uses its own control loop implementation."
}

